28 return Shuffle::make_slice(e, l, 0, 1);

31/** Find the exact max and min lanes of a vector expression. Not
32 * conservative like bounds_of_expr, but uses similar rules for some
33 * common node types where it can be exact. If e is a nested vector,
34 * the result will be the bounds of the vectors in each lane. */
35Interval bounds_of_nested_lanes(const Expr &e) {
36 if (const Add *add = e.as<Add>()) {
37 if (const Broadcast *b = add->b.as<Broadcast>()) {
38 Interval ia = bounds_of_nested_lanes(add->a);
39 return {ia.min + b->value, ia.max + b->value};
40 } else if (const Broadcast *b = add->a.as<Broadcast>()) {
41 Interval ia = bounds_of_nested_lanes(add->b);
42 return {b->value + ia.min, b->value + ia.max};
43 }
44 } else if (const Sub *sub = e.as<Sub>()) {
45 if (const Broadcast *b = sub->b.as<Broadcast>()) {
46 Interval ia = bounds_of_nested_lanes(sub->a);
47 return {ia.min - b->value, ia.max - b->value};
48 } else if (const Broadcast *b = sub->a.as<Broadcast>()) {
49 Interval ia = bounds_of_nested_lanes(sub->b);
50 return {b->value - ia.max, b->value - ia.max};
51 }
52 } else if (const Mul *mul = e.as<Mul>()) {
53 if (const Broadcast *b = mul->b.as<Broadcast>()) {
54 if (is_positive_const(b->value)) {
55 Interval ia = bounds_of_nested_lanes(mul->a);
56 return {ia.min * b->value, ia.max * b->value};
57 } else if (is_negative_const(b->value)) {
58 Interval ia = bounds_of_nested_lanes(mul->a);
59 return {ia.max * b->value, ia.min * b->value};
60 }
61 } else if (const Broadcast *b = mul->a.as<Broadcast>()) {
62 if (is_positive_const(b->value)) {
63 Interval ia = bounds_of_nested_lanes(mul->b);
64 return {b->value * ia.min, b->value * ia.max};
65 } else if (is_negative_const(b->value)) {
66 Interval ia = bounds_of_nested_lanes(mul->b);
67 return {b->value * ia.max, b->value * ia.min};
68 }
69 }
70 } else if (const Div *div = e.as<Div>()) {
71 if (const Broadcast *b = div->b.as<Broadcast>()) {
72 if (is_positive_const(b->value)) {
73 Interval ia = bounds_of_nested_lanes(div->a);
74 return {ia.min / b->value, ia.max / b->value};
75 } else if (is_negative_const(b->value)) {
76 Interval ia = bounds_of_nested_lanes(div->a);
77 return {ia.max / b->value, ia.min / b->value};
78 }
79 }
80 } else if (const And *and_ = e.as<And>()) {
81 if (const Broadcast *b = and_->b.as<Broadcast>()) {
82 Interval ia = bounds_of_nested_lanes(and_->a);
83 return {ia.min && b->value, ia.max && b->value};
84 } else if (const Broadcast *b = and_->a.as<Broadcast>()) {
85 Interval ia = bounds_of_nested_lanes(and_->b);
86 return {ia.min && b->value, ia.max && b->value};
87 }
88 } else if (const Or *or_ = e.as<Or>()) {
89 if (const Broadcast *b = or_->b.as<Broadcast>()) {
90 Interval ia = bounds_of_nested_lanes(or_->a);
91 return {ia.min && b->value, ia.max && b->value};
92 } else if (const Broadcast *b = or_->a.as<Broadcast>()) {
93 Interval ia = bounds_of_nested_lanes(or_->b);
94 return {ia.min && b->value, ia.max && b->value};
95 }
96 } else if (const Min *min = e.as<Min>()) {
97 if (const Broadcast *b = min->b.as<Broadcast>()) {
98 Interval ia = bounds_of_nested_lanes(min->a);
99 return {Min::make(ia.min, b->value), Min::make(ia.max, b->value)};
100 } else if (const Broadcast *b = min->a.as<Broadcast>()) {
101 Interval ia = bounds_of_nested_lanes(min->b);
102 return {Min::make(ia.min, b->value), Min::make(ia.max, b->value)};
103 }
104 } else if (const Max *max = e.as<Max>()) {
105 if (const Broadcast *b = max->b.as<Broadcast>()) {
106 Interval ia = bounds_of_nested_lanes(max->a);
107 return {Max::make(ia.min, b->value), Max::make(ia.max, b->value)};
108 } else if (const Broadcast *b = max->a.as<Broadcast>()) {
109 Interval ia = bounds_of_nested_lanes(max->b);
110 return {Max::make(ia.min, b->value), Max::make(ia.max, b->value)};
111 }
112 } else if (const Not *not_ = e.as<Not>()) {
113 Interval ia = bounds_of_nested_lanes(not_->a);
114 return {!ia.max, !ia.min};
115 } else if (const Ramp *r = e.as<Ramp>()) {
116 Expr last_lane_idx = make_const(r->base.type(), r->lanes - 1);
117 if (is_positive_const(r->stride)) {
118 return {r->base, r->base + last_lane_idx * r->stride};
119 } else if (is_negative_const(r->stride)) {
120 return {r->base + last_lane_idx * r->stride, r->base};
121 }
122 } else if (const LE *le = e.as<LE>()) {
123 // The least true this can be is if we maximize the LHS and minimize the RHS.
124 // The most true this can be is if we minimize the LHS and maximize the RHS.
125 // This is only exact if one of the two sides is a Broadcast.
126 Interval ia = bounds_of_nested_lanes(le->a);
127 Interval ib = bounds_of_nested_lanes(le->b);
128 if (ia.is_single_point() || ib.is_single_point()) {
129 return {ia.max <= ib.min, ia.min <= ib.max};
130 }
131 } else if (const LT *lt = e.as<LT>()) {
132 // The least true this can be is if we maximize the LHS and minimize the RHS.
133 // The most true this can be is if we minimize the LHS and maximize the RHS.
134 // This is only exact if one of the two sides is a Broadcast.
135 Interval ia = bounds_of_nested_lanes(lt->a);
136 Interval ib = bounds_of_nested_lanes(lt->b);
137 if (ia.is_single_point() || ib.is_single_point()) {
138 return {ia.max < ib.min, ia.min < ib.max};
139 }
140
141 } else if (const Broadcast *b = e.as<Broadcast>()) {
142 return {b->value, b->value};
143 } else if (const Let *let = e.as<Let>()) {
144 Interval ia = bounds_of_nested_lanes(let->value);
145 Interval ib = bounds_of_nested_lanes(let->body);
146 if (expr_uses_var(ib.min, let->name)) {
147 ib.min = Let::make(let->name, let->value, ib.min);
148 }
149 if (expr_uses_var(ib.max, let->name)) {
150 ib.max = Let::make(let->name, let->value, ib.max);
151 }
152 return ib;
153 }
154
155 // If all else fails, just take the explicit min and max over the
156 // lanes
157 if (e.type().is_bool()) {
158 Expr min_lane = VectorReduce::make(VectorReduce::And, e, 1);
159 Expr max_lane = VectorReduce::make(VectorReduce::Or, e, 1);
160 return {min_lane, max_lane};
161 } else {
162 Expr min_lane = VectorReduce::make(VectorReduce::Min, e, 1);
163 Expr max_lane = VectorReduce::make(VectorReduce::Max, e, 1);
164 return {min_lane, max_lane};
165 }
166};
167
168/** Similar to bounds_of_nested_lanes, but it recursively reduces
169 * the bounds of nested vectors to scalars. */
170Interval bounds_of_lanes(const Expr &e) {
171 Interval bounds = bounds_of_nested_lanes(e);
172 if (!bounds.min.type().is_scalar()) {
173 bounds.min = bounds_of_lanes(bounds.min).min;
174 }
175 if (!bounds.max.type().is_scalar()) {
176 bounds.max = bounds_of_lanes(bounds.max).max;
177 }
178 return bounds;
179}

181// A ramp with the lanes repeated inner_repetitions times, and then
182// the whole vector repeated outer_repetitions times.
183// E.g: <0 0 2 2 4 4 6 6 0 0 2 2 4 4 6 6>.
184struct InterleavedRamp {
185 Expr base, stride;
186 int lanes, inner_repetitions, outer_repetitions;
187};
188
189bool equal_or_zero(int a, int b) {
190 return a == 0 || b == 0 || a == b;
191}
192
193bool is_interleaved_ramp(const Expr &e, const Scope<Expr> &scope, InterleavedRamp *result) {
194 if (const Ramp *r = e.as<Ramp>()) {
195 const Broadcast *b_base = r->base.as<Broadcast>();
196 const Broadcast *b_stride = r->stride.as<Broadcast>();
197 if (r->base.type().is_scalar()) {
198 result->base = r->base;
199 result->stride = r->stride;
200 result->lanes = r->lanes;
201 result->inner_repetitions = 1;
202 result->outer_repetitions = 1;
203 return true;
204 } else if (b_base && b_stride && b_base->lanes == b_stride->lanes) {
205 // Ramp of broadcast
206 result->base = b_base->value;
207 result->stride = b_stride->value;
208 result->lanes = r->lanes;
209 result->inner_repetitions = b_base->lanes;
210 result->outer_repetitions = 1;
211 return true;
212 }
213 } else if (const Broadcast *b = e.as<Broadcast>()) {
214 if (b->value.type().is_scalar()) {
215 result->base = b->value;
216 result->stride = 0;
217 result->lanes = b->lanes;
218 result->inner_repetitions = 0;
219 result->outer_repetitions = 0;
220 return true;
221 } else if (is_interleaved_ramp(b->value, scope, result)) {
222 // Broadcast of interleaved ramp
223 result->outer_repetitions *= b->lanes;
224 return true;
225 }
226 } else if (const Add *add = e.as<Add>()) {
227 InterleavedRamp ra;
228 if (is_interleaved_ramp(add->a, scope, &ra) &&
229 is_interleaved_ramp(add->b, scope, result) &&
230 equal_or_zero(ra.inner_repetitions, result->inner_repetitions) &&
231 equal_or_zero(ra.outer_repetitions, result->outer_repetitions)) {
232 result->base = simplify(result->base + ra.base);
233 result->stride = simplify(result->stride + ra.stride);
234 result->inner_repetitions = std::max(result->inner_repetitions, ra.inner_repetitions);
235 result->outer_repetitions = std::max(result->outer_repetitions, ra.outer_repetitions);
236 return true;
237 }
238 } else if (const Sub *sub = e.as<Sub>()) {
239 InterleavedRamp ra;
240 if (is_interleaved_ramp(sub->a, scope, &ra) &&
241 is_interleaved_ramp(sub->b, scope, result) &&
242 equal_or_zero(ra.inner_repetitions, result->inner_repetitions) &&
243 equal_or_zero(ra.outer_repetitions, result->outer_repetitions)) {
244 result->base = simplify(ra.base - result->base);
245 result->stride = simplify(ra.stride - result->stride);
246 result->inner_repetitions = std::max(result->inner_repetitions, ra.inner_repetitions);
247 result->outer_repetitions = std::max(result->outer_repetitions, ra.outer_repetitions);
248 return true;
249 }
250 } else if (const Mul *mul = e.as<Mul>()) {
251 const int64_t *b = nullptr;
252 if (is_interleaved_ramp(mul->a, scope, result) &&
253 (b = as_const_int(mul->b))) {
254 result->base = simplify(result->base * (int)(*b));
255 result->stride = simplify(result->stride * (int)(*b));
256 return true;
257 }
258 } else if (const Div *div = e.as<Div>()) {
259 const int64_t *b = nullptr;
260 if (is_interleaved_ramp(div->a, scope, result) &&
261 (b = as_const_int(div->b)) &&
262 is_const_one(result->stride) &&
263 (result->inner_repetitions == 1 ||
264 result->inner_repetitions == 0) &&
265 can_prove((result->base % (int)(*b)) == 0)) {
266 // TODO: Generalize this. Currently only matches
267 // ramp(base*b, 1, lanes) / b
268 // broadcast(base * b, lanes) / b
269 result->base = simplify(result->base / (int)(*b));
270 result->inner_repetitions *= (int)(*b);
271 return true;
272 }
273 } else if (const Mod *mod = e.as<Mod>()) {
274 const int64_t *b = nullptr;
275 if (is_interleaved_ramp(mod->a, scope, result) &&
276 (b = as_const_int(mod->b)) &&
277 (result->outer_repetitions == 1 ||
278 result->outer_repetitions == 0) &&
279 can_prove(((int)(*b) % result->stride) == 0)) {
280 // ramp(base, 2, lanes) % 8
281 result->base = simplify(result->base % (int)(*b));
282 result->stride = simplify(result->stride % (int)(*b));
283 result->outer_repetitions *= (int)(*b);
284 return true;
285 }
286 } else if (const Variable *var = e.as<Variable>()) {
287 if (scope.contains(var->name)) {
288 return is_interleaved_ramp(scope.get(var->name), scope, result);
289 }
290 }
291 return false;
292}

294// Allocations inside vectorized loops grow an additional inner
295// dimension to represent the separate copy of the allocation per
296// vector lane. This means loads and stores to them need to be
297// rewritten slightly.
298class RewriteAccessToVectorAlloc : public IRMutator {
299 Expr var;
300 string alloc;
301 int lanes;
302
303 using IRMutator::visit;
304
305 Expr mutate_index(const string &a, Expr index) {
306 index = mutate(index);
307 if (a == alloc) {
308 return index * lanes + var;
309 } else {
310 return index;
311 }
312 }
313
314 ModulusRemainder mutate_alignment(const string &a, const ModulusRemainder &align) {
315 if (a == alloc) {
316 return align * lanes;
317 } else {
318 return align;
319 }
320 }
321
322 Expr visit(const Load *op) override {
323 return Load::make(op->type, op->name, mutate_index(op->name, op->index),
324 op->image, op->param, mutate(op->predicate), mutate_alignment(op->name, op->alignment));
325 }
326
327 Stmt visit(const Store *op) override {
328 return Store::make(op->name, mutate(op->value), mutate_index(op->name, op->index),
329 op->param, mutate(op->predicate), mutate_alignment(op->name, op->alignment));
330 }
331
332public:
333 RewriteAccessToVectorAlloc(const string &v, string a, int l)
334 : var(Variable::make(Int(32), v)), alloc(std::move(a)), lanes(l) {
335 }
336};

348public:
349 bool uses_gpu = false;

352bool uses_gpu_vars(const Expr &s) {

371// Wrap a vectorized predicate around a Load/Store node.
372class PredicateLoadStore : public IRMutator {
373 string var;
374 Expr vector_predicate;
375 bool is_explicit;
376 bool in_hexagon;
377 const Target &target;
378 int lanes;
379 bool valid;
380 bool vectorized;
381
382 using IRMutator::visit;
383
384 bool should_predicate_store_load(int bit_size) {
385 if (is_explicit) {
386 return true;
387 } else if (in_hexagon) {
388 internal_assert(target.has_feature(Target::HVX))
389 << "We are inside a hexagon loop, but the target doesn't have hexagon's features\n";
390 return true;
391 } else if (target.arch == Target::X86) {
392 // Should only attempt to predicate store/load if the lane size is
393 // no less than 4
394 // TODO: disabling for now due to trunk LLVM breakage.
395 // See: https://github.com/halide/Halide/issues/3534
396 // return (bit_size == 32) && (lanes >= 4);
397 return false;
398 }
399 // For other architecture, do not predicate vector load/store
400 return false;
401 }
402
403 Expr merge_predicate(Expr pred, const Expr &new_pred) {
404 if (pred.type().lanes() == new_pred.type().lanes()) {
405 Expr res = simplify(pred && new_pred);
406 return res;
407 }
408 valid = false;
409 return pred;
410 }
411
412 Expr visit(const Load *op) override {
413 valid = valid && op->predicate.type().lanes() == lanes;
414 valid = valid && should_predicate_store_load(op->type.bits());
415 if (!valid) {
416 return op;
417 }
418
419 Expr predicate, index;
420 if (!op->index.type().is_scalar()) {
421 internal_assert(op->predicate.type().lanes() == lanes);
422 internal_assert(op->index.type().lanes() == lanes);
423
424 predicate = mutate(op->predicate);
425 index = mutate(op->index);
426 } else if (expr_uses_var(op->index, var)) {
427 predicate = mutate(Broadcast::make(op->predicate, lanes));
428 index = mutate(Broadcast::make(op->index, lanes));
429 } else {
430 return IRMutator::visit(op);
431 }
432
433 predicate = merge_predicate(predicate, vector_predicate);
434 if (!valid) {
435 return op;
436 }
437 vectorized = true;
438 return Load::make(op->type, op->name, index, op->image, op->param, predicate, op->alignment);
439 }
440
441 Stmt visit(const Store *op) override {
442 valid = valid && op->predicate.type().lanes() == lanes;
443 valid = valid && should_predicate_store_load(op->value.type().bits());
444 if (!valid) {
445 return op;
446 }
447
448 Expr predicate, value, index;
449 if (!op->index.type().is_scalar()) {
450 internal_assert(op->predicate.type().lanes() == lanes);
451 internal_assert(op->index.type().lanes() == lanes);
452 internal_assert(op->value.type().lanes() == lanes);
453
454 predicate = mutate(op->predicate);
455 value = mutate(op->value);
456 index = mutate(op->index);
457 } else if (expr_uses_var(op->index, var)) {
458 predicate = mutate(Broadcast::make(op->predicate, lanes));
459 value = mutate(Broadcast::make(op->value, lanes));
460 index = mutate(Broadcast::make(op->index, lanes));
461 } else {
462 return IRMutator::visit(op);
463 }
464
465 predicate = merge_predicate(predicate, vector_predicate);
466 if (!valid) {
467 return op;
468 }
469 vectorized = true;
470 return Store::make(op->name, value, index, op->param, predicate, op->alignment);
471 }
472
473 Expr visit(const Call *op) override {
474 // We should not vectorize calls with side-effects
475 valid = valid && op->is_pure();
476 return IRMutator::visit(op);
477 }
478
479public:
480 PredicateLoadStore(string v, const Expr &vpred, bool is_explicit, bool in_hexagon, const Target &t)
481 : var(std::move(v)), vector_predicate(vpred), is_explicit(is_explicit), in_hexagon(in_hexagon),
482 target(t), lanes(vpred.type().lanes()), valid(true), vectorized(false) {
483 internal_assert(lanes > 1);
484 }
485
486 bool is_vectorized() const {
487 return valid && vectorized;
488 }
489};

499// Substitutes a vector for a scalar var in a Stmt. Used on the
500// body of every vectorized loop.
501class VectorSubs : public IRMutator {
502 // A list of vectorized loop vars encountered so far. The last
503 // element corresponds to the most inner vectorized loop.
504 std::vector<VectorizedVar> vectorized_vars;
505
506 // What we're replacing it with. Usually a combination of ramps
507 // and broadcast. It depends on the current loop level and
508 // is updated when vectorized_vars list is updated.
509 std::map<string, Expr> replacements;
510
511 const Target &target;
512
513 bool in_hexagon; // Are we inside the hexagon loop?
514
515 // A scope containing lets and letstmts whose values became
516 // vectors. Contains are original, non-vectorized expressions.
517 Scope<Expr> scope;
518
519 // Based on the same set of Exprs, but indexed by the vectorized
520 // var name and holding vectorized expression.
521 Scope<Expr> vector_scope;
522
523 // A stack of all containing lets. We need to reinject the scalar
524 // version of them if we scalarize inner code.
525 vector<pair<string, Expr>> containing_lets;
526
527 // Widen an expression to the given number of lanes.
528 Expr widen(Expr e, int lanes) {
529 if (e.type().lanes() == lanes) {
530 return e;
531 } else if (lanes % e.type().lanes() == 0) {
532 return Broadcast::make(e, lanes / e.type().lanes());
533 } else {
534 internal_error << "Mismatched vector lanes in VectorSubs " << e.type().lanes()
535 << " " << lanes << "\n";
536 }
537 return Expr();
538 }
539
540 using IRMutator::visit;
541
542 Expr visit(const Cast *op) override {
543 Expr value = mutate(op->value);
544 if (value.same_as(op->value)) {
545 return op;
546 } else {
547 Type t = op->type.with_lanes(value.type().lanes());
548 return Cast::make(t, value);
549 }
550 }
551
552 string get_widened_var_name(const string &name) {
553 return name + ".widened." + vectorized_vars.back().name;
554 }
555
556 Expr visit(const Variable *op) override {
557 if (replacements.count(op->name) > 0) {
558 return replacements[op->name];
559 } else if (scope.contains(op->name)) {
560 string widened_name = get_widened_var_name(op->name);
561 return Variable::make(vector_scope.get(widened_name).type(), widened_name);
562 } else {
563 return op;
564 }
565 }
566
567 template<typename T>
568 Expr mutate_binary_operator(const T *op) {
569 Expr a = mutate(op->a), b = mutate(op->b);
570 if (a.same_as(op->a) && b.same_as(op->b)) {
571 return op;
572 } else {
573 int w = std::max(a.type().lanes(), b.type().lanes());
574 return T::make(widen(a, w), widen(b, w));
575 }
576 }
577
578 Expr visit(const Add *op) override {
579 return mutate_binary_operator(op);
580 }
581 Expr visit(const Sub *op) override {
582 return mutate_binary_operator(op);
583 }
584 Expr visit(const Mul *op) override {
585 return mutate_binary_operator(op);
586 }
587 Expr visit(const Div *op) override {
588 return mutate_binary_operator(op);
589 }
590 Expr visit(const Mod *op) override {
591 return mutate_binary_operator(op);
592 }
593 Expr visit(const Min *op) override {
594 return mutate_binary_operator(op);
595 }
596 Expr visit(const Max *op) override {
597 return mutate_binary_operator(op);
598 }
599 Expr visit(const EQ *op) override {
600 return mutate_binary_operator(op);
601 }
602 Expr visit(const NE *op) override {
603 return mutate_binary_operator(op);
604 }
605 Expr visit(const LT *op) override {
606 return mutate_binary_operator(op);
607 }
608 Expr visit(const LE *op) override {
609 return mutate_binary_operator(op);
610 }
611 Expr visit(const GT *op) override {
612 return mutate_binary_operator(op);
613 }
614 Expr visit(const GE *op) override {
615 return mutate_binary_operator(op);
616 }
617 Expr visit(const And *op) override {
618 return mutate_binary_operator(op);
619 }
620 Expr visit(const Or *op) override {
621 return mutate_binary_operator(op);
622 }
623
624 Expr visit(const Select *op) override {
625 Expr condition = mutate(op->condition);
626 Expr true_value = mutate(op->true_value);
627 Expr false_value = mutate(op->false_value);
628 if (condition.same_as(op->condition) &&
629 true_value.same_as(op->true_value) &&
630 false_value.same_as(op->false_value)) {
631 return op;
632 } else {
633 int lanes = std::max(true_value.type().lanes(), false_value.type().lanes());
634 lanes = std::max(lanes, condition.type().lanes());
635 // Widen the true and false values, but we don't have to widen the condition
636 true_value = widen(true_value, lanes);
637 false_value = widen(false_value, lanes);
638 return Select::make(condition, true_value, false_value);
639 }
640 }
641
642 Expr visit(const Load *op) override {
643 Expr predicate = mutate(op->predicate);
644 Expr index = mutate(op->index);
645
646 if (predicate.same_as(op->predicate) && index.same_as(op->index)) {
647 return op;
648 } else {
649 int w = index.type().lanes();
650 predicate = widen(predicate, w);
651 return Load::make(op->type.with_lanes(w), op->name, index, op->image,
652 op->param, predicate, op->alignment);
653 }
654 }
655
656 Expr visit(const Call *op) override {
657 // Widen the call by changing the lanes of all of its
658 // arguments and its return type
659 vector<Expr> new_args(op->args.size());
660 bool changed = false;
661
662 // Mutate the args
663 int max_lanes = 0;
664 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->args.size(); i++) {
665 Expr old_arg = op->args[i];
666 Expr new_arg = mutate(old_arg);
667 if (!new_arg.same_as(old_arg)) {
668 changed = true;
669 }
670 new_args[i] = new_arg;
671 max_lanes = std::max(new_arg.type().lanes(), max_lanes);
672 }
673
674 if (!changed) {
675 return op;
676 } else if (op->name == Call::trace) {
677 const int64_t *event = as_const_int(op->args[6]);
678 internal_assert(event != nullptr);
679 if (*event == halide_trace_begin_realization || *event == halide_trace_end_realization) {
680 // Call::trace vectorizes uniquely for begin/end realization, because the coordinates
681 // for these are actually min/extent pairs; we need to maintain the proper dimensionality
682 // count and instead aggregate the widened values into a single pair.
683 for (size_t i = 1; i <= 2; i++) {
684 const Call *make_struct = Call::as_intrinsic(new_args[i], {Call::make_struct});
685 internal_assert(make_struct);
686 if (i == 1) {
687 // values should always be empty for these events
688 internal_assert(make_struct->args.empty());
689 continue;
690 }
691 vector<Expr> call_args(make_struct->args.size());
692 for (size_t j = 0; j < call_args.size(); j += 2) {
693 Expr min_v = widen(make_struct->args[j], max_lanes);
694 Expr extent_v = widen(make_struct->args[j + 1], max_lanes);
695 Expr min_scalar = get_lane(min_v, 0);
696 Expr max_scalar = min_scalar + get_lane(extent_v, 0);
697 for (int k = 1; k < max_lanes; ++k) {
698 Expr min_k = get_lane(min_v, k);
699 Expr extent_k = get_lane(extent_v, k);
700 min_scalar = min(min_scalar, min_k);
701 max_scalar = max(max_scalar, min_k + extent_k);
702 }
703 call_args[j] = min_scalar;
704 call_args[j + 1] = max_scalar - min_scalar;
705 }
706 new_args[i] = Call::make(make_struct->type.element_of(), Call::make_struct, call_args, Call::Intrinsic);
707 }
708 } else {
709 // Call::trace vectorizes uniquely, because we want a
710 // single trace call for the entire vector, instead of
711 // scalarizing the call and tracing each element.
712 for (size_t i = 1; i <= 2; i++) {
713 // Each struct should be a struct-of-vectors, not a
714 // vector of distinct structs.
715 const Call *make_struct = Call::as_intrinsic(new_args[i], {Call::make_struct});
716 internal_assert(make_struct);
717 // Widen the call args to have the same lanes as the max lanes found
718 vector<Expr> call_args(make_struct->args.size());
719 for (size_t j = 0; j < call_args.size(); j++) {
720 call_args[j] = widen(make_struct->args[j], max_lanes);
721 }
722 new_args[i] = Call::make(make_struct->type.element_of(), Call::make_struct,
723 call_args, Call::Intrinsic);
724 }
725 // One of the arguments to the trace helper
726 // records the number of vector lanes in the type being
727 // stored.
728 new_args[5] = max_lanes;
729 // One of the arguments to the trace helper
730 // records the number entries in the coordinates (which we just widened)
731 if (max_lanes > 1) {
732 new_args[9] = new_args[9] * max_lanes;
733 }
734 }
735 return Call::make(op->type, Call::trace, new_args, op->call_type);
736 } else {
737 // Widen the args to have the same lanes as the max lanes found
738 for (size_t i = 0; i < new_args.size(); i++) {
739 new_args[i] = widen(new_args[i], max_lanes);
740 }
741 return Call::make(op->type.with_lanes(max_lanes), op->name, new_args,
742 op->call_type, op->func, op->value_index, op->image, op->param);
743 }
744 }
745
746 Expr visit(const Let *op) override {
747 // Vectorize the let value and check to see if it was vectorized by
748 // this mutator. The type of the expression might already be vector
749 // width.
750 Expr mutated_value = simplify(mutate(op->value));
751 bool was_vectorized = (!op->value.type().is_vector() &&
752 mutated_value.type().is_vector());
753
754 // If the value was vectorized by this mutator, add a new name to
755 // the scope for the vectorized value expression.
756 string vectorized_name;
757 if (was_vectorized) {
758 vectorized_name = get_widened_var_name(op->name);
759 scope.push(op->name, op->value);
760 vector_scope.push(vectorized_name, mutated_value);
761 }
762
763 Expr mutated_body = mutate(op->body);
764
765 InterleavedRamp ir;
766 if (is_interleaved_ramp(mutated_value, vector_scope, &ir)) {
767 return substitute(vectorized_name, mutated_value, mutated_body);
768 } else if (mutated_value.same_as(op->value) &&
769 mutated_body.same_as(op->body)) {
770 return op;
771 } else if (was_vectorized) {
772 scope.pop(op->name);
773 vector_scope.pop(vectorized_name);
774 return Let::make(vectorized_name, mutated_value, mutated_body);
775 } else {
776 return Let::make(op->name, mutated_value, mutated_body);
777 }
778 }
779
780 Stmt visit(const LetStmt *op) override {
781 Expr mutated_value = simplify(mutate(op->value));
782 string vectorized_name = op->name;
783
784 // Check if the value was vectorized by this mutator.
785 bool was_vectorized = (!op->value.type().is_vector() &&
786 mutated_value.type().is_vector());
787
788 if (was_vectorized) {
789 vectorized_name = get_widened_var_name(op->name);
790 scope.push(op->name, op->value);
791 vector_scope.push(vectorized_name, mutated_value);
792 // Also keep track of the original let, in case inner code scalarizes.
793 containing_lets.emplace_back(op->name, op->value);
794 }
795
796 Stmt mutated_body = mutate(op->body);
797
798 if (was_vectorized) {
799 containing_lets.pop_back();
800 scope.pop(op->name);
801 vector_scope.pop(vectorized_name);
802 }
803
804 InterleavedRamp ir;
805 if (is_interleaved_ramp(mutated_value, vector_scope, &ir)) {
806 return substitute(vectorized_name, mutated_value, mutated_body);
807 } else if (mutated_value.same_as(op->value) &&
808 mutated_body.same_as(op->body)) {
809 return op;
810 } else {
811 return LetStmt::make(vectorized_name, mutated_value, mutated_body);
812 }
813 }

816 internal_error << "Vectorizing a Provide node is unimplemented. "
817 << "Vectorization usually runs after storage flattening.\n";
818 return Stmt();
819 }

832 }

838
839 Stmt visit(const IfThenElse *op) override {
840 Expr cond = mutate(op->condition);
841 int lanes = cond.type().lanes();
842
843 bool explicit_predicate = false;
844 if (const Call *pred = Call::as_intrinsic(cond, {Call::predicate})) {
845 explicit_predicate = true;
846 cond = pred->args[0];
847 }
848
849 debug(3) << "Vectorizing \n"
850 << "Old: " << op->condition << "\n"
851 << "New: " << cond << "\n";
852
853 Stmt then_case = mutate(op->then_case);
854 Stmt else_case = mutate(op->else_case);
855
856 if (lanes > 1) {
857 // We have an if statement with a vector condition,
858 // which would mean control flow divergence within the
859 // SIMD lanes.
860
861 bool vectorize_predicate =
862 explicit_predicate || !(uses_gpu_vars(cond) || (vectorized_vars.size() > 1));
863
864 Stmt predicated_stmt;
865 if (vectorize_predicate) {
866 PredicateLoadStore p(vectorized_vars.front().name, cond, explicit_predicate, in_hexagon, target);
867 predicated_stmt = p.mutate(then_case);
868 vectorize_predicate = p.is_vectorized();
869 }
870 if (vectorize_predicate && else_case.defined()) {
871 PredicateLoadStore p(vectorized_vars.front().name, !cond, explicit_predicate, in_hexagon, target);
872 predicated_stmt = Block::make(predicated_stmt, p.mutate(else_case));
873 vectorize_predicate = p.is_vectorized();
874 }
875
876 debug(4) << "IfThenElse should vectorize predicate "
877 << "? " << vectorize_predicate << "; cond: " << cond << "\n";
878 debug(4) << "Predicated stmt:\n"
879 << predicated_stmt << "\n";
880
881 // First check if the condition is marked as likely.
882 if (const Call *likely = Call::as_intrinsic(cond, {Call::likely, Call::likely_if_innermost})) {
883
884 // The meaning of the likely intrinsic is that
885 // Halide should optimize for the case in which
886 // *every* likely value is true. We can do that by
887 // generating a scalar condition that checks if
888 // the least-true lane is true.
889 Expr all_true = bounds_of_lanes(likely->args[0]).min;
890 // Wrap it in the same flavor of likely
891 all_true = Call::make(Bool(), likely->name,
892 {all_true}, Call::PureIntrinsic);
893
894 if (!vectorize_predicate) {
895 // We should strip the likelies from the case
896 // that's going to scalarize, because it's no
897 // longer likely.
898 Stmt without_likelies =
899 IfThenElse::make(unwrap_tags(op->condition),
900 op->then_case, op->else_case);
901
902 // scalarize() will put back all vectorized loops around the statement as serial,
903 // but it still may happen that there are vectorized loops inside of the statement
904 // itself which we may want to handle. All the context is invalid though, so
905 // we just start anew for this specific statement.
906 Stmt scalarized = scalarize(without_likelies, false);
907 scalarized = vectorize_statement(scalarized, target);
908 Stmt stmt =
909 IfThenElse::make(all_true,
910 then_case,
911 scalarized);
912 debug(4) << "...With all_true likely: \n"
913 << stmt << "\n";
914 return stmt;
915 } else {
916 Stmt stmt =
917 IfThenElse::make(all_true,
918 then_case,
919 predicated_stmt);
920 debug(4) << "...Predicated IfThenElse: \n"
921 << stmt << "\n";
922 return stmt;
923 }
924 } else {
925 // It's some arbitrary vector condition.
926 if (!vectorize_predicate) {
927 debug(4) << "...Scalarizing vector predicate: \n"
928 << Stmt(op) << "\n";
929 return scalarize(op);
930 } else {
931 Stmt stmt = predicated_stmt;
932 debug(4) << "...Predicated IfThenElse: \n"
933 << stmt << "\n";
934 return stmt;
935 }
936 }
937 } else {
938 // It's an if statement on a scalar, we're ok to vectorize the innards.
939 debug(3) << "Not scalarizing if then else\n";
940 if (cond.same_as(op->condition) &&
941 then_case.same_as(op->then_case) &&
942 else_case.same_as(op->else_case)) {
943 return op;
944 } else {
945 return IfThenElse::make(cond, then_case, else_case);
946 }
947 }
948 }
949
950 Stmt visit(const For *op) override {
951 ForType for_type = op->for_type;
952
953 Expr min = mutate(op->min);
954 Expr extent = mutate(op->extent);
955
956 Stmt body = op->body;
957
958 if (min.type().is_vector()) {
959 // Rebase the loop to zero and try again
960 Expr var = Variable::make(Int(32), op->name);
961 Stmt body = substitute(op->name, var + op->min, op->body);
962 Stmt transformed = For::make(op->name, 0, op->extent, for_type, op->device_api, body);
963 return mutate(transformed);
964 }
965
966 if (extent.type().is_vector()) {
967 // We'll iterate up to the max over the lanes, but
968 // inject an if statement inside the loop that stops
969 // each lane from going too far.
970
971 extent = bounds_of_lanes(extent).max;
972 Expr var = Variable::make(Int(32), op->name);
973 body = IfThenElse::make(likely(var < op->min + op->extent), body);
974 }
975
976 if (op->for_type == ForType::Vectorized) {
977 const IntImm *extent_int = extent.as<IntImm>();
978 if (!extent_int || extent_int->value <= 1) {
979 user_error << "Loop over " << op->name
980 << " has extent " << extent
981 << ". Can only vectorize loops over a "
982 << "constant extent > 1\n";
983 }
984
985 vectorized_vars.push_back({op->name, min, (int)extent_int->value});
986 update_replacements();
987 // Go over lets which were vectorized and update them according to the current
988 // loop level.
989 for (auto it = scope.cbegin(); it != scope.cend(); ++it) {
990 string vectorized_name = get_widened_var_name(it.name());
991 Expr vectorized_value = mutate(it.value());
992 vector_scope.push(vectorized_name, vectorized_value);
993 }
994
995 body = mutate(body);
996
997 // Append vectorized lets for this loop level.
998 for (auto it = scope.cbegin(); it != scope.cend(); ++it) {
999 string vectorized_name = get_widened_var_name(it.name());
1000 Expr vectorized_value = vector_scope.get(vectorized_name);
1001 vector_scope.pop(vectorized_name);
1002 InterleavedRamp ir;
1003 if (is_interleaved_ramp(vectorized_value, vector_scope, &ir)) {
1004 body = substitute(vectorized_name, vectorized_value, body);
1005 } else {
1006 body = LetStmt::make(vectorized_name, vectorized_value, body);
1007 }
1008 }
1009 vectorized_vars.pop_back();
1010 update_replacements();
1011 return body;
1012 } else {
1013 body = mutate(body);
1014
1015 if (min.same_as(op->min) &&
1016 extent.same_as(op->extent) &&
1017 body.same_as(op->body) &&
1018 for_type == op->for_type) {
1019 return op;
1020 } else {
1021 return For::make(op->name, min, extent, for_type, op->device_api, body);
1022 }
1023 }
1024 }
1025
1026 Stmt visit(const Allocate *op) override {
1027 vector<Expr> new_extents;
1028 Expr new_expr;
1029
1030 // The new expanded dimensions are innermost.
1031 for (const auto &vv : vectorized_vars) {
1032 new_extents.emplace_back(vv.lanes);
1033 }
1034
1035 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->extents.size(); i++) {
1036 Expr extent = mutate(op->extents[i]);
1037 // For vector sizes, take the max over the lanes. Note
1038 // that we haven't changed the strides, which also may
1039 // vary per lane. This is a bit weird, but the way we
1040 // set up the vectorized memory means that lanes can't
1041 // clobber each others' memory, so it doesn't matter.
1042 if (extent.type().is_vector()) {
1043 extent = bounds_of_lanes(extent).max;
1044 }
1045 new_extents.push_back(extent);
1046 }
1047
1048 if (op->new_expr.defined()) {
1049 new_expr = mutate(op->new_expr);
1050 user_assert(new_expr.type().is_scalar())
1051 << "Cannot vectorize an allocation with a varying new_expr per vector lane.\n";
1052 }
1053
1054 Stmt body = op->body;
1055
1056 // Rewrite loads and stores to this allocation like so:
1057 // foo[x] -> foo[x*lanes + v]
1058 for (const auto &vv : vectorized_vars) {
1059 body = RewriteAccessToVectorAlloc(vv.name + ".from_zero", op->name, vv.lanes).mutate(body);
1060 }
1061
1062 body = mutate(body);
1063
1064 for (const auto &vv : vectorized_vars) {
1065 // The variable itself could still exist inside an inner scalarized block.
1066 body = substitute(vv.name + ".from_zero", Variable::make(Int(32), vv.name), body);
1067 }
1068
1069 return Allocate::make(op->name, op->type, op->memory_type, new_extents, op->condition, body, new_expr, op->free_function);
1070 }
1071
1072 Stmt visit(const Atomic *op) override {
1073 // Recognize a few special cases that we can handle as within-vector reduction trees.
1074 do {
1075 if (!op->mutex_name.empty()) {
1076 // We can't vectorize over a mutex
1077 break;
1078 }
1079
1080 // f[x] = f[x] <op> y
1081 const Store *store = op->body.as<Store>();
1082 if (!store) {
1083 break;
1084 }
1085
1086 VectorReduce::Operator reduce_op = VectorReduce::Add;
1087 Expr a, b;
1088 if (const Add *add = store->value.as<Add>()) {
1089 a = add->a;
1090 b = add->b;
1091 reduce_op = VectorReduce::Add;
1092 } else if (const Mul *mul = store->value.as<Mul>()) {
1093 a = mul->a;
1094 b = mul->b;
1095 reduce_op = VectorReduce::Mul;
1096 } else if (const Min *min = store->value.as<Min>()) {
1097 a = min->a;
1098 b = min->b;
1099 reduce_op = VectorReduce::Min;
1100 } else if (const Max *max = store->value.as<Max>()) {
1101 a = max->a;
1102 b = max->b;
1103 reduce_op = VectorReduce::Max;
1104 } else if (const Cast *cast_op = store->value.as<Cast>()) {
1105 if (cast_op->type.element_of() == UInt(8) &&
1106 cast_op->value.type().is_bool()) {
1107 if (const And *and_op = cast_op->value.as<And>()) {
1108 a = and_op->a;
1109 b = and_op->b;
1110 reduce_op = VectorReduce::And;
1111 } else if (const Or *or_op = cast_op->value.as<Or>()) {
1112 a = or_op->a;
1113 b = or_op->b;
1114 reduce_op = VectorReduce::Or;
1115 }
1116 }
1117 } else if (const Call *call_op = store->value.as<Call>()) {
1118 if (call_op->is_intrinsic(Call::saturating_add)) {
1119 a = call_op->args[0];
1120 b = call_op->args[1];
1121 reduce_op = VectorReduce::SaturatingAdd;
1122 }
1123 }
1124
1125 if (!a.defined() || !b.defined()) {
1126 break;
1127 }
1128
1129 // Bools get cast to uint8 for storage. Strip off that
1130 // cast around any load.
1131 if (b.type().is_bool()) {
1132 const Cast *cast_op = b.as<Cast>();
1133 if (cast_op) {
1134 b = cast_op->value;
1135 }
1136 }
1137 if (a.type().is_bool()) {
1138 const Cast *cast_op = b.as<Cast>();
1139 if (cast_op) {
1140 a = cast_op->value;
1141 }
1142 }
1143
1144 if (a.as<Variable>() && !b.as<Variable>()) {
1145 std::swap(a, b);
1146 }
1147
1148 // We require b to be a var, because it should have been lifted.
1149 const Variable *var_b = b.as<Variable>();
1150 const Load *load_a = a.as<Load>();
1151
1152 if (!var_b ||
1153 !scope.contains(var_b->name) ||
1154 !load_a ||
1155 load_a->name != store->name ||
1156 !is_const_one(load_a->predicate) ||
1157 !is_const_one(store->predicate)) {
1158 break;
1159 }
1160
1161 b = vector_scope.get(get_widened_var_name(var_b->name));
1162 Expr store_index = mutate(store->index);
1163 Expr load_index = mutate(load_a->index);
1164
1165 // The load and store indices must be the same interleaved
1166 // ramp (or the same scalar, in the total reduction case).
1167 InterleavedRamp store_ir, load_ir;
1168 Expr test;
1169 if (store_index.type().is_scalar()) {
1170 test = simplify(load_index == store_index);
1171 } else if (is_interleaved_ramp(store_index, vector_scope, &store_ir) &&
1172 is_interleaved_ramp(load_index, vector_scope, &load_ir) &&
1173 store_ir.inner_repetitions == load_ir.inner_repetitions &&
1174 store_ir.outer_repetitions == load_ir.outer_repetitions &&
1175 store_ir.lanes == load_ir.lanes) {
1176 test = simplify(store_ir.base == load_ir.base &&
1177 store_ir.stride == load_ir.stride);
1178 }
1179
1180 if (!test.defined()) {
1181 break;
1182 }
1183
1184 if (is_const_zero(test)) {
1185 break;
1186 } else if (!is_const_one(test)) {
1187 // TODO: try harder by substituting in more things in scope
1188 break;
1189 }
1190
1191 auto binop = [=](const Expr &a, const Expr &b) {
1192 switch (reduce_op) {
1193 case VectorReduce::Add:
1194 return a + b;
1195 case VectorReduce::Mul:
1196 return a * b;
1197 case VectorReduce::Min:
1198 return min(a, b);
1199 case VectorReduce::Max:
1200 return max(a, b);
1201 case VectorReduce::And:
1202 return a && b;
1203 case VectorReduce::Or:
1204 return a || b;
1205 case VectorReduce::SaturatingAdd:
1206 return saturating_add(a, b);
1207 }
1208 return Expr();
1209 };
1210
1211 int output_lanes = 1;
1212 if (store_index.type().is_scalar()) {
1213 // The index doesn't depend on the value being
1214 // vectorized, so it's a total reduction.
1215
1216 b = VectorReduce::make(reduce_op, b, 1);
1217 } else {
1218
1219 output_lanes = store_index.type().lanes() / (store_ir.inner_repetitions * store_ir.outer_repetitions);
1220
1221 store_index = Ramp::make(store_ir.base, store_ir.stride, output_lanes / store_ir.base.type().lanes());
1222 if (store_ir.inner_repetitions > 1) {
1223 b = VectorReduce::make(reduce_op, b, output_lanes * store_ir.outer_repetitions);
1224 }
1225
1226 // Handle outer repetitions by unrolling the reduction
1227 // over slices.
1228 if (store_ir.outer_repetitions > 1) {
1229 // First remove all powers of two with a binary reduction tree.
1230 int reps = store_ir.outer_repetitions;
1231 while (reps % 2 == 0) {
1232 int l = b.type().lanes() / 2;
1233 Expr b0 = Shuffle::make_slice(b, 0, 1, l);
1234 Expr b1 = Shuffle::make_slice(b, l, 1, l);
1235 b = binop(b0, b1);
1236 reps /= 2;
1237 }
1238
1239 // Then reduce linearly over slices for the rest.
1240 if (reps > 1) {
1241 Expr v = Shuffle::make_slice(b, 0, 1, output_lanes);
1242 for (int i = 1; i < reps; i++) {
1243 Expr slice = simplify(Shuffle::make_slice(b, i * output_lanes, 1, output_lanes));
1244 v = binop(v, slice);
1245 }
1246 b = v;
1247 }
1248 }
1249 }
1250
1251 Expr new_load = Load::make(load_a->type.with_lanes(output_lanes),
1252 load_a->name, store_index, load_a->image,
1253 load_a->param, const_true(output_lanes),
1254 ModulusRemainder{});
1255
1256 Expr lhs = cast(b.type(), new_load);
1257 b = binop(lhs, b);
1258 b = cast(new_load.type(), b);
1259
1260 Stmt s = Store::make(store->name, b, store_index, store->param,
1261 const_true(b.type().lanes()), store->alignment);
1262
1263 // We may still need the atomic node, if there was more
1264 // parallelism than just the vectorization.
1265 s = Atomic::make(op->producer_name, op->mutex_name, s);
1266
1267 return s;
1268 } while (false);
1269
1270 // In the general case, if a whole stmt has to be done
1271 // atomically, we need to serialize.
1272 return scalarize(op);
1273 }
1274
1275 Stmt scalarize(Stmt s, bool serialize_inner_loops = true) {
1276 // Wrap a serial loop around it. Maybe LLVM will have
1277 // better luck vectorizing it.
1278
1279 if (serialize_inner_loops) {
1280 s = SerializeLoops().mutate(s);
1281 }
1282 // We'll need the original scalar versions of any containing lets.
1283 for (size_t i = containing_lets.size(); i > 0; i--) {
1284 const auto &l = containing_lets[i - 1];
1285 s = LetStmt::make(l.first, l.second, s);
1286 }
1287
1288 for (int ix = vectorized_vars.size() - 1; ix >= 0; ix--) {
1289 s = For::make(vectorized_vars[ix].name, vectorized_vars[ix].min,
1290 vectorized_vars[ix].lanes, ForType::Serial, DeviceAPI::None, s);
1291 }
1292
1293 return s;
1294 }
1295
1296 Expr scalarize(Expr e) {
1297 // This method returns a select tree that produces a vector lanes
1298 // result expression
1299 user_assert(replacements.size() == 1) << "Can't scalarize nested vectorization\n";
1300 string var = replacements.begin()->first;
1301 Expr replacement = replacements.begin()->second;
1302
1303 Expr result;
1304 int lanes = replacement.type().lanes();
1305
1306 for (int i = lanes - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
1307 // Hide all the vector let values in scope with a scalar version
1308 // in the appropriate lane.
1309 for (Scope<Expr>::const_iterator iter = scope.cbegin(); iter != scope.cend(); ++iter) {
1310 e = substitute(iter.name(),
1311 get_lane(Variable::make(iter.value().type(), iter.name()), i),
1312 e);
1313 }
1314
1315 // Replace uses of the vectorized variable with the extracted
1316 // lane expression
1317 e = substitute(var, i, e);
1318
1319 if (i == lanes - 1) {
1320 result = Broadcast::make(e, lanes);
1321 } else {
1322 Expr cond = (replacement == Broadcast::make(i, lanes));
1323 result = Select::make(cond, Broadcast::make(e, lanes), result);
1324 }
1325 }
1326
1327 return result;
1328 }
1329
1330 // Recompute all replacements for vectorized vars based on
1331 // the current stack of vectorized loops.
1332 void update_replacements() {
1333 replacements.clear();
1334
1335 for (const auto &var : vectorized_vars) {
1336 // Two different replacements are needed for each loop var
1337 // one starting from zero and another starting from loop.min.
1338 replacements[var.name] = var.min;
1339 replacements[var.name + ".from_zero"] = 0;
1340 }
1341
1342 Expr strided_ones = 1;
1343 for (int ix = vectorized_vars.size() - 1; ix >= 0; ix--) {
1344 for (int ik = 0; ik < (int)vectorized_vars.size(); ik++) {
1345 if (ix == ik) {
1346 replacements[vectorized_vars[ik].name] =
1347 Ramp::make(replacements[vectorized_vars[ik].name],
1348 strided_ones,
1349 vectorized_vars[ix].lanes);
1350 replacements[vectorized_vars[ik].name + ".from_zero"] =
1351 Ramp::make(replacements[vectorized_vars[ik].name + ".from_zero"],
1352 strided_ones,
1353 vectorized_vars[ix].lanes);
1354 } else {
1355 replacements[vectorized_vars[ik].name] =
1356 Broadcast::make(replacements[vectorized_vars[ik].name],
1357 vectorized_vars[ix].lanes);
1358 replacements[vectorized_vars[ik].name + ".from_zero"] =
1359 Broadcast::make(replacements[vectorized_vars[ik].name + ".from_zero"],
1360 vectorized_vars[ix].lanes);
1361 }
1362 }
1363
1364 strided_ones = Broadcast::make(strided_ones, vectorized_vars[ix].lanes);
1365 }
1366 }
1367
1368public:
1369 VectorSubs(const VectorizedVar &vv, bool in_hexagon, const Target &t)
1370 : target(t), in_hexagon(in_hexagon) {
1371 vectorized_vars.push_back(vv);
1372 update_replacements();
1373 }
1374}; // namespace

1376class FindVectorizableExprsInAtomicNode : public IRMutator {
1377 // An Atomic node protects all accesses to a given buffer. We
1378 // consider a name "poisoned" if it depends on an access to this
1379 // buffer. We can't lift or vectorize anything that has been
1380 // poisoned.
1381 Scope<> poisoned_names;
1382 bool poison = false;
1383
1384 using IRMutator::visit;
1385
1386 template<typename T>
1387 const T *visit_let(const T *op) {
1388 mutate(op->value);
1389 ScopedBinding<> bind_if(poison, poisoned_names, op->name);
1390 mutate(op->body);
1391 return op;
1392 }
1393
1394 Stmt visit(const LetStmt *op) override {
1395 return visit_let(op);
1396 }
1397
1398 Expr visit(const Let *op) override {
1399 return visit_let(op);
1400 }
1401
1402 Expr visit(const Load *op) override {
1403 // Even if the load is bad, maybe we can lift the index
1404 IRMutator::visit(op);
1405
1406 poison |= poisoned_names.contains(op->name);
1407 return op;
1408 }
1409
1410 Expr visit(const Variable *op) override {
1411 poison = poisoned_names.contains(op->name);
1412 return op;
1413 }
1414
1415 Stmt visit(const Store *op) override {
1416 // A store poisons all subsequent loads, but loads before the
1417 // first store can be lifted.
1418 mutate(op->index);
1419 mutate(op->value);
1420 poisoned_names.push(op->name);
1421 return op;
1422 }
1423
1424 Expr visit(const Call *op) override {
1425 IRMutator::visit(op);
1426 // unsafe_promise_clamped and similar isn't pure because it's
1427 // not safe to lift it out of if statements. If *is* safe to
1428 // lift it out of atomic nodes though.
1429 poison |= !(op->is_pure() ||
1430 op->is_intrinsic(Call::unsafe_promise_clamped) ||
1431 op->is_intrinsic(Call::promise_clamped));
1432 return op;
1433 }
1434
1435public:
1436 using IRMutator::mutate;
1437
1438 Expr mutate(const Expr &e) override {
1439 bool old_poison = poison;
1440 poison = false;
1441 IRMutator::mutate(e);
1442 if (!poison) {
1443 liftable.insert(e);
1444 }
1445 poison |= old_poison;
1446 // We're not actually mutating anything. This class is only a
1447 // mutator so that we can override a generic mutate() method.
1448 return e;
1449 }
1450
1451 FindVectorizableExprsInAtomicNode(const string &buf, const map<string, Function> &env) {
1452 poisoned_names.push(buf);
1453 auto it = env.find(buf);
1454 if (it != env.end()) {
1455 // Handle tuples
1456 size_t n = it->second.values().size();
1457 if (n > 1) {
1458 for (size_t i = 0; i < n; i++) {
1459 poisoned_names.push(buf + "." + std::to_string(i));
1460 }
1461 }
1462 }
1463 }
1464
1465 std::set<Expr, ExprCompare> liftable;
1466};
1467
1468class LiftVectorizableExprsOutOfSingleAtomicNode : public IRMutator {
1469 const std::set<Expr, ExprCompare> &liftable;
1470
1471 using IRMutator::visit;
1472
1473 template<typename StmtOrExpr, typename LetStmtOrLet>
1474 StmtOrExpr visit_let(const LetStmtOrLet *op) {
1475 if (liftable.count(op->value)) {
1476 // Lift it under its current name to avoid having to
1477 // rewrite the variables in other lifted exprs.
1478 // TODO: duplicate non-overlapping liftable let stmts due to unrolling.
1479 lifted.emplace_back(op->name, op->value);
1480 return mutate(op->body);
1481 } else {
1482 return IRMutator::visit(op);
1483 }
1484 }
1485
1486 Stmt visit(const LetStmt *op) override {
1487 return visit_let<Stmt>(op);
1488 }
1489
1490 Expr visit(const Let *op) override {
1491 return visit_let<Expr>(op);
1492 }
1493
1494public:
1495 map<Expr, string, IRDeepCompare> already_lifted;
1496 vector<pair<string, Expr>> lifted;
1497
1498 using IRMutator::mutate;
1499
1500 Expr mutate(const Expr &e) override {
1501 if (liftable.count(e) && !is_const(e) && !e.as<Variable>()) {
1502 auto it = already_lifted.find(e);
1503 string name;
1504 if (it != already_lifted.end()) {
1505 name = it->second;
1506 } else {
1507 name = unique_name('t');
1508 lifted.emplace_back(name, e);
1509 already_lifted.emplace(e, name);
1510 }
1511 return Variable::make(e.type(), name);
1512 } else {
1513 return IRMutator::mutate(e);
1514 }
1515 }
1516
1517 LiftVectorizableExprsOutOfSingleAtomicNode(const std::set<Expr, ExprCompare> &liftable)
1518 : liftable(liftable) {
1519 }
1520};
1521
1522class LiftVectorizableExprsOutOfAllAtomicNodes : public IRMutator {
1523 using IRMutator::visit;
1524
1525 Stmt visit(const Atomic *op) override {
1526 FindVectorizableExprsInAtomicNode finder(op->producer_name, env);
1527 finder.mutate(op->body);
1528 LiftVectorizableExprsOutOfSingleAtomicNode lifter(finder.liftable);
1529 Stmt new_body = lifter.mutate(op->body);
1530 new_body = Atomic::make(op->producer_name, op->mutex_name, new_body);
1531 while (!lifter.lifted.empty()) {
1532 auto p = lifter.lifted.back();
1533 new_body = LetStmt::make(p.first, p.second, new_body);
1534 lifter.lifted.pop_back();
1535 }
1536 return new_body;
1537 }
1538
1539 const map<string, Function> &env;
1540
1541public:
1542 LiftVectorizableExprsOutOfAllAtomicNodes(const map<string, Function> &env)
1543 : env(env) {
1544 }
1545};

1547// Vectorize all loops marked as such in a Stmt
1548class VectorizeLoops : public IRMutator {
1549 const Target &target;
1550 bool in_hexagon;
1551
1552 using IRMutator::visit;
1553
1554 Stmt visit(const For *for_loop) override {
1555 bool old_in_hexagon = in_hexagon;
1556 if (for_loop->device_api == DeviceAPI::Hexagon) {
1557 in_hexagon = true;
1558 }
1559
1560 Stmt stmt;
1561 if (for_loop->for_type == ForType::Vectorized) {
1562 const IntImm *extent = for_loop->extent.as<IntImm>();
1563 if (!extent || extent->value <= 1) {
1564 user_error << "Loop over " << for_loop->name
1565 << " has extent " << for_loop->extent
1566 << ". Can only vectorize loops over a "
1567 << "constant extent > 1\n";
1568 }
1569
1570 VectorizedVar vectorized_var = {for_loop->name, for_loop->min, (int)extent->value};
1571 stmt = VectorSubs(vectorized_var, in_hexagon, target).mutate(for_loop->body);
1572 } else {
1573 stmt = IRMutator::visit(for_loop);
1574 }
1575
1576 if (for_loop->device_api == DeviceAPI::Hexagon) {
1577 in_hexagon = old_in_hexagon;
1578 }
1579
1580 return stmt;
1581 }
1582
1583public:
1584 VectorizeLoops(const Target &t)
1585 : target(t), in_hexagon(false) {
1586 }
1587};

1589/** Check if all stores in a Stmt are to names in a given scope. Used
1590 by RemoveUnnecessaryAtomics below. */
1591class AllStoresInScope : public IRVisitor {
1592 using IRVisitor::visit;
1593 void visit(const Store *op) override {
1594 result = result && s.contains(op->name);
1595 }
1596
1597public:
1598 bool result = true;
1599 const Scope<> &s;
1600 AllStoresInScope(const Scope<> &s)
1601 : s(s) {
1602 }
1603};
1604bool all_stores_in_scope(const Stmt &stmt, const Scope<> &scope) {
1605 AllStoresInScope checker(scope);
1606 stmt.accept(&checker);
1607 return checker.result;
1608}

1610/** Drop any atomic nodes protecting buffers that are only accessed
1611 * from a single thread. */
1612class RemoveUnnecessaryAtomics : public IRMutator {
1613 using IRMutator::visit;
1614
1615 // Allocations made from within this same thread
1616 bool in_thread = false;
1617 Scope<> local_allocs;
1618
1619 Stmt visit(const Allocate *op) override {
1620 ScopedBinding<> bind(local_allocs, op->name);
1621 return IRMutator::visit(op);
1622 }
1623
1624 Stmt visit(const Atomic *op) override {
1625 if (!in_thread || all_stores_in_scope(op->body, local_allocs)) {
1626 return mutate(op->body);
1627 } else {
1628 return op;
1629 }
1630 }
1631
1632 Stmt visit(const For *op) override {
1633 if (is_parallel(op->for_type)) {
1634 ScopedValue<bool> old_in_thread(in_thread, true);
1635 Scope<> old_local_allocs;
1636 old_local_allocs.swap(local_allocs);
1637 Stmt s = IRMutator::visit(op);
1638 old_local_allocs.swap(local_allocs);
1639 return s;
1640 } else {
1641 return IRMutator::visit(op);
1642 }
1643 }
1644};
1645
1646class RemovePredicateHints : public IRMutator {
1647 using IRMutator::visit;
1648
1649 Expr visit(const Call *op) override {
1650 if (op->is_intrinsic(Call::predicate)) {
1651 return op->args[0];
1652 } else {
1653 return IRMutator::visit(op);
1654 }
1655 }
1656};
1657
1658Stmt vectorize_statement(const Stmt &stmt, const Target &t) {
1659 return VectorizeLoops(t).mutate(stmt);
1660}
1661
1662} // namespace
1663Stmt vectorize_loops(const Stmt &stmt, const map<string, Function> &env, const Target &t) {
1664 // Limit the scope of atomic nodes to just the necessary stuff.
1665 // TODO: Should this be an earlier pass? It's probably a good idea
1666 // for non-vectorizing stuff too.
1667 Stmt s = LiftVectorizableExprsOutOfAllAtomicNodes(env).mutate(stmt);
1668 s = vectorize_statement(s, t);
1669 s = RemoveUnnecessaryAtomics().mutate(s);
1670 s = RemovePredicateHints().mutate(s);
1671 return s;
1672}
